## This session: author a new ENSEMBLE

You are authoring a new ensemble catalogue entry under
`catalogue/ensembles/<name>/`. An ensemble is a complete R2-DEF §7 unit:
a class string + sentants + plugins + UI registrations + capability
declarations. It binds to one role within an apiary.

## Read these FIRST, in this order

1. `specifications/SPEC-CATALOGUE-LAYOUT.md` §4 — **the normative
   ensemble-authoring spec**. The `ensemble.yaml` schema (top-level key
   `ensemble:`, REQUIRED sub-keys), the `ENSEMBLE.md` H2 section list,
   the `AI-CONTEXT.md` structure, validation rules.

2. `specifications/SPEC-APIARY-COMPOSE.md` §2 — the role-ensemble model
   that explains how this ensemble will eventually be referenced by an
   apiary's `[[role_ensembles]]`.

3. The canonical example: `catalogue/ensembles/rocker-sensor/`. Read
   `ensemble.yaml` (15 sentants + 12 plugins), `ENSEMBLE.md`,
   `AI-CONTEXT.md`. Note the substrate-vs-domain distinction (most
   sentants are reusable substrate; ONE is the deployment-specific
   domain logic).

4. Upstream R2 references cited by §4:
   - R2-ENSEMBLE §2.1.2 (ensemble-owned vs hive-shared plugins).
   - R2-DEF §7 (ensemble score schema).
   - R2-DEF §7.10 (load-time validation).
   - R2-CAP §3 (reverse-DNS class convention).

## What you MUST produce

Per SPEC-CATALOGUE-LAYOUT §4.1:

- `catalogue/ensembles/<name>/ensemble.yaml` — full R2-DEF §7 score.
- `catalogue/ensembles/<name>/ENSEMBLE.md` — 8 H2 sections per §4.4.
- `catalogue/ensembles/<name>/AI-CONTEXT.md` — 9 H2 sections per §4.5.
- `catalogue/ensembles/<name>/sentants/` — at least one sentant
  subdirectory (one per `ensemble.sentants[]` entry). EACH sentant
  conforms to SPEC-CATALOGUE-LAYOUT §6 (separate authoring step —
  may follow this one).
- `catalogue/ensembles/<name>/plugins/` — OPTIONAL — only for
  ensemble-owned plugins (per R2-ENSEMBLE §2.1.2). Each plugin conforms
  to §5.
- `catalogue/ensembles/<name>/conversation/<date>-author-ensemble-NN.md`
  — transcript.

## Constraints

- Directory name = `ensemble.name` in kebab-case (e.g. `rocker-sensor`).
- Class string is reverse-DNS per R2-CAP §3 (NOT prefixed automatically
  by `ai.reality2.*` — operator chooses the namespace; e.g.
  `nz.ac.auckland.rocker`).
- `compile_target` array MUST overlap with at least one carrier in
  `catalogue/boards/`.
- Plugin references in sentants are by NAME or by CAPABILITY string
  (per R2-PLUGIN §10). Capability-references survive carrier swaps;
  prefer them for the domain-relevant sentant binding (e.g. the
  Accelerometer sentant binds `ai.reality2.cap.accel.triaxial`, not
  `adxl355`).
- Per SPEC-APIARY-COMPOSE [[project-multi-board-apiary-compose]]: an
  ensemble's `plugins[]` lists the capability requirements; the per-
  target plugin choices live in the APIARY's `[[role_ensembles.targets.plugin_overrides]]`.

## How to ask clarifying questions

What role does this ensemble fulfil (sensor / controller / viewer /
keyholder / other)? What target type (mcu-fw / native / beam / wasm)?
What capabilities does it require from the carrier? What events does
it emit / consume across the apiary's other role-ensembles? Is there
a deployment-specific domain sentant + reusable substrate sentants
distinction (per the rocker-sensor convention)?

